Step 1 — Create project folder
    + mkdir manufacturing-traceability-platform
    + cd manufacturing-traceability-platform
    + mkdir backend 
    + mkdir frontend

Step 2 — Backend choice
    + Backend: Django + Django REST Framework
    + Database: MySQL
    + Frontend: Angular
    + Auth: JWT

Step 3 — Create Django backend
    + cd backend
    + python -m venv venv
    + venv\Scripts\activate
    + pip install django djangorestframework mysqlclient djangorestframework-simplejwt django-cors-headers
    + django-admin startproject config .
    + python manage.py startapp traceability

Step 4 — Configure settings.py
    + Add apps:
    INSTALLED_APPS = [
        ...
        "rest_framework",
        "corsheaders",
        "traceability",
    ]

    + Add middleware:
    MIDDLEWARE = [
        "corsheaders.middleware.CorsMiddleware",
        ...
    ]

    + Allow Angular:
    CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS = [
        "http://localhost:4200",
    ]

    + JWT config:
    REST_FRAMEWORK = {
        "DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES": (
            "rest_framework_simplejwt.authentication.JWTAuthentication",
        ),
    }

Step 5 — Create database models in traceability/models.py.

Step 6 — Run migration
    + Create a dedicated MySQL user
        Login to MySQL using whatever admin account works, then run:

        CREATE DATABASE traceability_db;
        CREATE USER 'trace_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'trace_password';
        GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON traceability_db.* TO 'trace_user'@'localhost';
        FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
    
    + python manage.py makemigrations
    + python manage.py migrate
    + python manage.py createsuperuser     # admin user (ddi)

Step 7: Check if backend server django is running ok
    + python manage.py runserver

    If we got error "Error: You don't have permission to access that port.". Try to run with another port (e.g. python manage.py runserver 8001)

    + http://127.0.0.1:8001/ to check server



